===Music===

The ''Iris'' [[Soundtrack|original soundtrack]] was released as a 16-track album on November 13, 2009, with music composed by Yi Dong-jun and Choe Seong-gwon. The soundtrack contained a number of the vocal themes used in the series, including those by [[Baek Ji-young]], [[Shin Seung Hun|Shin Seung-hun]], and Big Bang.<ref>{{ko icon}} {{cite news | author= | url=http://music.daum.net/album/album.do?albumId=489890 | title= <U+C544><U+C774><U+B9AC><U+C2A4>(Iris) O.S.T | work=Daum | date= | accessdate=2010-04-23}}</ref><ref>{{ko icon}} {{cite news | author= | url=http://www.maniadb.com/album.asp?a=400055 | title=<U+C544><U+C774><U+B9AC><U+C2A4> ost | work=ManiaDB | date= | accessdate=2010-04-23}}</ref>

On December 24, a limited edition was released as a two-disc set with a 76-page photobook. The first disc contained ten vocal themes, four of which were used in the second half of the series and not included on the original release. The second disc collected fifteen instrumentals used as backdrops during the show's run, including four not on the previous collection.<ref>{{cite news | author= | url=http://www.yesasia.com/us/iris-ost-special-2cd-kbs-tv-drama/1021865233-0-0-0-en/info.html | title=IRIS OST Special (2CD) (KBS TV Drama) | work=YesAsia | date= | accessdate=2010-04-23}}</ref>

In the week preceding the premiere of ''Iris'' on Japanese television, it was announced that Big Bang would be contributing an all-new [[ballad]] to be inserted into the TBS airings. Titled "Tell Me Goodbye," the song is also set to be released as a single in the country on June 9, 2010,<ref>{{cite news | author=Han Sang-hee | url=http://www.koreatimes.co.kr/www/news/special/2010/04/139_64472.html | title= Big Bang to Sing Theme Song for IRIS | work=The Korea Times | date=2009-04-19 | accessdate=2010-04-30}}</ref> and will be available in both a CD and a CD & DVD edition.<ref name=Shin1>{{ja icon}} {{cite news | author= | url=http://www.shinseido.co.jp/tv/overseas/iris.html | title=SHINSEIDO SHOPPING SITE - IRIS -<U+30A2><U+30A4><U+30EA><U+30B9>  | work=Shinseido Shopping Site | date=2010-04-28 | accessdate=2010-04-30}}</ref>

Coinciding with the initial broadcast of the series in Japan, a deluxe soundtrack box-set is scheduled for a May 26, 2010 release. In addition to featuring thirteen vocal themes and nineteen instrumentals, the release will include a 72-page photobook adapted from the previous Korean release.<ref name=Shin1>{{ja icon}} {{cite news | author= | url=http://www.shinseido.co.jp/tv/overseas/iris.html | title=SHINSEIDO SHOPPING SITE - IRIS -<U+30A2><U+30A4><U+30EA><U+30B9>  | work=Shinseido Shopping Site | date=2010-04-28 | accessdate=2010-04-30}}</ref>

