===Novelization===

A two-volume novelization was published prior to and during the show's initial run. Written by Chae Woo-do, the first volume was published on October 12, 2009, two days prior to the show's premiere on KBS.<ref>{{ko icon}} {{cite news | author= | url=http://book.naver.com/bookdb/book_detail.nhn?bid=6095145 | title=Naver: <U+C544><U+C774><U+B9AC><U+C2A4>  1 | work=Naver Books | date= | accessdate=2010-04-23}}</ref> The second volume was published exactly one month later on November 12,<ref>{{ko icon}} {{cite news | author= | url=http://book.11st.co.kr/Goods.do?cmd=detail&gdsNo=M0000000625718 | title=Naver: <U+C544><U+C774><U+B9AC><U+C2A4>  2 | work=Naver Books | date= | accessdate=2010-04-23}}</ref> and, unlike its predecessor, did not follow the eventual plot of the television series.<ref>{{ko icon}} {{cite news | author= | url=http://kr.news.yahoo.com/service/news/shellview.htm?articleid=20091128160317554b0&linkid=63&newssetid=487 | title=<U+C18C><U+C124> <U+2018><U+C544><U+C774><U+B9AC><U+C2A4><U+2019> <U+BC1C><U+AC04>, <U+AE40><U+D0DC><U+D76C>-<U+C774><U+BCD1><U+D5CC> <U+2018><U+D574><U+D53C><U+C5D4><U+B529><U+2019> <U+ACB0><U+B9D0> <U+ACF5><U+AC1C>? | work=Yahoo News Korea | date=2009-11-28 | accessdate=2010-04-23}}</ref><ref>{{ko icon}} {{cite news | author= | url=http://clubsprint.tistory.com/4383 | title=<U+C544><U+C774><U+B9AC><U+C2A4> <U+ACB0><U+B9D0>, <U+C6D0><U+C791> <U+C18C><U+C124><U+C740> <U+C5B4><U+B5A8><U+AE4C>? | work=TVExciting | date=2009-12-04 | accessdate=2010-04-23}}</ref><ref>{{ko icon}} {{cite news | author= | url=http://tvexciting.com/1074 | title=<U+CD5C><U+C2B9><U+D76C> <U+C815><U+CCB4> <U+BBF8><U+C2A4><U+D14C><U+B9AC>, <U+C544><U+C774><U+B9AC><U+C2A4> <U+ACB0><U+B9D0><U+C5D0> <U+BC18><U+C804>? <U+D639>, <U+B300><U+D1B5><U+B839><U+C774> <U+C544><U+C774><U+B9AC><U+C2A4>? | work=TVExciting | date= | accessdate=2010-04-23}}</ref>

===Home video===

''Iris'' was released on [[DVD region 3#Region codes and countries|Region 3 DVD]] in South Korea on February 12, 2010 in an 8-disc set, complete with English subtitles. The first pressing included a 50-page photobook with previously unpublished photographs from the production of the series.<ref>{{ko icon}} {{cite news | author= | url=http://www.esportsi.com/bbs/zboard.php?id=tv01&page=8&sn1=on&divpage=1&sn=on&ss=off&sc=off&keyword=%BF%AC%BF%B9%BD%BA%C6%F7%C3%F7&select_arrange=headnum&desc=asc&no=3741 | title=<<U+C544><U+C774><U+B9AC><U+C2A4>> (IRIS) <U+D504><U+B9AC><U+BBF8><U+C5C4> DVD <U+BC1C><U+B9E4>! | work=ESportsI | date=2009-02-01 | accessdate=2010-04-21}}</ref><ref>{{cite news | author= | url=http://www.yesasia.com/global/1021967371-0-0-0-en/info.html | title=Iris (DVD) (8-Disc) (English Subtitled) (KBS TV Drama) (Premium Limited Edition) (Korea Version) | work=YesAsia | date= | accessdate=2010-04-21}}</ref>

Earlier, on November 27, 2009, a 100-minute making-of documentary titled ''Iris Navigate DVD'' was released for the Japanese market, documenting the filming of the series in Hungary, Japan, and Korea.<ref>{{ja icon}} {{cite news | author= | url=http://www.byung-hun.com/info/index.asp?id=681 | title=<U+30A2><U+30A4><U+30EA><U+30B9><U+30CA><U+30D3><U+30B2><U+30FC><U+30C8>DVD <U+767A><U+58F2><U+6C7A><U+5B9A>! | work=Lee Byung Hun: Japan Official Fanclub | date=2009-10-23 | accessdate=2010-04-21}}</ref>

The full series is set to be released over two uncut DVD box-sets in Japan. The first has been announced for release on July 2, 2010 and will retail for 19,950 yen ($212 USD), with the second to follow September 15. On August 3, 2010, the first volume will be released on [[Blu-ray]] with the second coming October 20th, both priced at 25,200 yen ($268 USD). The first pressings will include replica NSS ID cards, a postcard set, a bonus disc, and a 24-page data booklet.<ref name=TBS1>{{ja icon}} {{cite news | author= | url=http://www.tbs.co.jp/iris2010/news/#n2010042822 | title=TBS<U+300C>IRIS - <U+30A2><U+30A4><U+30EA><U+30B9><U+300D> <U+304A><U+77E5><U+3089><U+305B>  | work=TBS | date=2010-04-28 | accessdate=2010-04-30}}</ref><ref name=Shin1>{{ja icon}} {{cite news | author= | url=http://www.shinseido.co.jp/tv/overseas/iris.html | title=SHINSEIDO SHOPPING SITE - IRIS -<U+30A2><U+30A4><U+30EA><U+30B9>  | work=Shinseido Shopping Site | date=2010-04-28 | accessdate=2010-04-30}}</ref>

In addition, two behind-the-scenes production diary box-sets are to be issued in Japan beginning June 16, 2010. The first follows the cast's filming in Akita and Hungary while the second tracks their work in Korea and is scheduled for September 15.<ref name=TBS1>{{ja icon}} {{cite news | author= | url=http://www.tbs.co.jp/iris2010/news/#n2010042822 | title=TBS<U+300C>IRIS - <U+30A2><U+30A4><U+30EA><U+30B9><U+300D> <U+304A><U+77E5><U+3089><U+305B>  | work=TBS | date=2010-04-28 | accessdate=2010-04-30}}</ref><ref name=Shin1>{{ja icon}} {{cite news | author= | url=http://www.shinseido.co.jp/tv/overseas/iris.html | title=SHINSEIDO SHOPPING SITE - IRIS -<U+30A2><U+30A4><U+30EA><U+30B9>  | work=Shinseido Shopping Site | date=2010-04-28 | accessdate=2010-04-30}}</ref>

==Awards and recognition==

''Iris'' was the top-rated program for its initial run and received strong ratings throughout, culminating in nearly 40% of the South Korean viewing audience tuning in for its finale.<ref>{{ko icon}} {{cite news | author=<U+AE40><U+C9C4><U+C6B1> | url=http://nownews.seoul.co.kr/news/newsView.php?id=20100326603015 | title=<U+CD94><U+B178>-<U+C120><U+B355><U+C5EC><U+C655>-<U+C544><U+C774><U+B9AC><U+C2A4>, <U+AC19><U+C740> <U+2018><U+C8FD><U+C74C><U+2019> <U+B2E4><U+B978> <U+2018><U+C5EC><U+C6B4><U+2019> | work=Net to News | date=2010-03-26 | accessdate=2010-04-30}}</ref>

The series and its actors won numerous awards at the 2009 [[KBS Drama Awards]], including Lee Byung-hun receiving the Daesang for his portrayal of Kim Hyun-jun. Kim Tae-hee was given the Excellence Award for an Actress, while Jung Joon-ho and Kim Seung-woo were both awarded the Excellence Award for an Actor for their work on the series. Yoon Joo-sang was named Best Supporting Actor, and Kim So-yeon was given the Popularity Award. Lee Byung-hun and Kim Tae-hee were one pair to win the Best Couple Award, and in addition, Lee was also honored with the Netizens' Award for an Actor.<ref name=ArtsNews1>{{ko icon}} {{cite news | author= | url=http://www.artsnews.co.kr/news/55892 | title= <U+C774><U+BCD1><U+D5CC>, 'KBS <U+C5F0><U+AE30><U+B300><U+C0C1>' 3<U+AD00><U+C655> <U+CC28><U+C9C0><U+D558><U+BA70> <U+C800><U+B825> <U+ACFC><U+C2DC>! | work=ArtsNews | date=2010-01-01 | accessdate=2010-04-21}}</ref>

At the 46th annual [[PaekSang Arts Awards]], Lee won for Best Actor and the series itself was awarded Best Drama.<ref name=PaekSang1>{{ko icon}} {{cite news | author= | url=http://isplus.joins.com/100sang/winners/winners_46.html | title=<U+C81C> 46<U+D68C> <U+BC31><U+C0C1><U+C608><U+C220><U+B300><U+C0C1>  | work=PaekSang Arts Awards | date=2010-03-26 | accessdate=2010-04-21}}</ref>

==Sequels==

A [[Spin-off (media)|spin-off]] series to be shot in 2010 and aired later in the year has been announced. Starring [[Soo Ae]], [[Jung Woo-sung]], [[Cha Seung-won]] and [[Lee Ji-ah]], the series is to be titled ''[[Athena: Goddess of War]]'' and will be filmed [[Filming location|on location]] in [[Italy]], [[Switzerland]], [[Singapore]], and [[New Zealand]] among others.<ref>{{ko icon}} {{cite news | author=<U+B0A8><U+C548><U+C6B0> | url=http://www.mydaily.co.kr/news/read.html?newsid=201003031138301119 | title=<U+C815><U+C6B0><U+C131><U+00B7><U+CC28><U+C2B9><U+C6D0>, <U+B4DC><U+B77C><U+B9C8> <U+2018><U+C544><U+C774><U+B9AC><U+C2A4>2<U+2019> <U+C8FC><U+C5F0> <U+BC1C><U+D0C1>  | work=MyDaily | date=2010-03-03 | accessdate=2010-04-21}}</ref><ref>{{ko icon}} {{cite news | author= | url=http://osen.mt.co.kr/news/view.html?gid=G1004090050 | title=<U+C218><U+C560>, '<U+C544><U+C774><U+B9AC><U+C2A4>' <U+C2A4><U+D540><U+C624><U+D504> '<U+C544><U+D14C><U+B098>' <U+C5EC><U+C8FC><U+C778><U+ACF5> <U+B099><U+C810>  | work=Osen | date=2010-04-09 | accessdate=2010-04-21}}</ref><ref>{{ko icon}} {{cite news | author= | url=http://star.mt.co.kr/view/stview.php?no=2010041511123479212 | title=<U+C774><U+C9C0><U+C544>, '<U+C544><U+C774><U+B9AC><U+C2A4>2' <U+D569><U+B958><U+2026><U+C218><U+C560><U+C640> <U+B9E4><U+B825><U+B300><U+ACB0>  | work=Star News | date=2010-04-15 | accessdate=2010-04-21}}</ref>

A true sequel series, tentatively titled ''Iris 2'' and set three years after the original, has been announced for October 2011. Pre-production is underway and filming is expected to commence in March 2011.<ref>{{cite news | author=Lynn Kim | url=http://10.asiae.co.kr/Articles/new_view.htm?sec=ent0&a_id=2010042016075086382 | title="IRIS" season 2 starts pre-production  | work=10 Asia | date=2010-04-20 | accessdate=2010-04-21}}</ref> As a direct continuation of the original series, stars of the original cast, including Lee Byung-hun, Kim Tae-hee, and Kim So-yeon, are expected to return.<ref>{{ko icon}} {{cite news | author= | url=http://star.mt.co.kr/stview.php?no=2010042011432295763 | title='<U+C544><U+C774><U+B9AC><U+C2A4>2' <U+B0B4><U+B144> 10<U+C6D4> <U+BC29><U+C1A1> "<U+C804><U+D3B8> <U+CD9C><U+C5F0><U+C790> <U+D611><U+C758><U+C911>"  | work=Star News | date=2010-04-20 | accessdate=2010-04-21}}</ref>

==Feature film==

'''''Iris: The Movie''''' is a feature length edit of the TV series for cinemas. While not featuring a differing story, additional scenes were shot that expanded upon the original storyline, including an all-new extended ending. The film received its premiere at the [[Hong Kong International Film Festival|34th Hong Kong International Film Festival]].<ref>{{ko icon}} {{cite news | author= | url=http://web.reviewstar.net/web_200806/view.php?id=227570&code=1030 | title=<U+2018><U+C544><U+C774><U+B9AC><U+C2A4><U+2019> <U+ADF9><U+C7A5><U+D310>, <U+C774><U+BCD1><U+D5CC> <U+C800><U+ACA9><U+BC94> <U+C815><U+CCB4> <U+ACF5><U+AC1C>  | work=ReviewStar | date=2010-03-26 | accessdate=2010-04-21}}</ref>

